    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 7.82,
      "end": 13.9,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 14.96,
      "end": 17.64,
      "text": "Recorded by Beth Dudek.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 19.24,
      "end": 22.56,
      "text": "ESOP's Fables, the Bat and the Weasels.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 24.62,
      "end": 33.64,
      "text": "A bat fell to the ground and was caught by a weasel, and was just going to be killed and eaten when it begged to be let go.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 34.48,
      "end": 39.34,
      "text": "The weasel said he couldn't do that because he was an enemy of all birds on principle.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 40.98,
      "end": 46.96,
      "text": "Oh, but! said the bat. I'm not a bird at all. I'm a mouse.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 48.86,
      "end": 55.3,
      "text": "So you are! said the weasel. Now I come to look at you. And he let it go.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 56.22,
      "end": 66.12,
      "text": "Sometime after this, the bat was caught in just the same way by another weasel, and, as before, begged for its life.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 67.62,
      "end": 72.92,
      "text": "No! said the weasel. I never let a mouse go by any chance.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 74.28,
      "end": 78.52,
      "text": "But I'm not a mouse! said the bat. I'm a bird.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 79.9,
      "end": 85.44,
      "text": "Why so you are! said the weasel. And he too let the bat go.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 86.64,
      "end": 91.14,
      "text": "Look and see which way the wind blows before you commit yourself.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 92.92,
      "end": 95.08,
      "text": "End of the bat and the weasels.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
